# LeakSanitizer suppressions for the c47/c43 simulator analysis lanes.
#
# AddressSanitizer is the hard memory gate (ITERATION-3 policy), but a few
# upstream allocations are made once at startup and never freed, so they would
# fail the gate on every run and hide a real regression. Suppress the known ones
# here - tight, by the allocating frame - so a NEW leak still fails the lane.
# Each entry is an upstream bug to file, not a harness defect.

# fnReset -> showSoftmenuCurrentPart -> initVariableSoftmenu ->
# _dynmenuConstructUser (src/c47/softmenus.c:1577): the dynamic VAR softmenu is
# malloc'd on reset and never freed (40 bytes, 1 allocation).
leak:_dynmenuConstructUser
